<plot>It is the Fall of 1999. A sudden barrage of terror attacks in Russia drives Prime Minister Vladimir Putin to order a second massive invasion of the breakaway republic of Chechnya. Dogadko (KEVIN CIRONE), a neophyte Russian soldier, finds himself lost in a world of lawlessness, inhumanity, and endless hatred. After a deadly falling out with his commanding officer (NATHAN HADLOCK), Dogadko flees into the Chechen wilderness. He soon encounters a strange Chechen girl named Ajmani (JENNIFER MAKHOLM) who grants him refuge in her isolated village. With a militant brother (JOHN SACKMAN) fighting against the Russian army, Ajmani cannot keep Dogadko's presence a secret forever.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?659796</url></doc>
